[[File:Veturilo Warszawa 03.jpg|thumb|upright|Veturilo station]]
'''Veturilo''' is a public [[bicycle sharing system]] in [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]], launched on 1 August 2012 with 55 stations and 1000 bicycles in 3 districts - [[<U+015A>r<U+00F3>dmie<U+015B>cie, Warsaw|<U+015A>r<U+00F3>dmie<U+015B>cie]] (city centre), [[Bielany]] and [[Ursyn<U+00F3>w]],<ref>{{en icon}} {{cite web |author= |url=http://ztm.waw.pl/aktualnosci.php?i=792&c=100&l=2 |title=Cycle with Veturilo in Warsaw |work=ztm.waw.pl |publisher=ZTM Warszawa |pages= |page= |date=2012-08-02 |accessdate=2012-08-26}}</ref> 2 other stations started operating in the middle of August in [[Wilan<U+00F3>w]].<ref>{{pl icon}} {{cite web |author= |url=http://www.veturilo.waw.pl/2012/08/17/zakrec-w-wilanowie/|title=Zakr<U+0119><U+0107> w Wilanowie |work=www.veturilo.waw.pl |publisher= |pages= |page= |date= |accessdate=2012-08-24}}</ref> It is the biggest public bicycle sharing system in Poland.<ref>{{pl icon}} {{cite web |author= |url=http://polskanarowery.sport.pl/msrowery/1,105126,11888605,Warszawa_bedzie_miala_rower_publiczny.html |title=Warszawa b<U+0119>dzie mia<U+0142>a rower publiczny |work=polskanarowery.sport.pl |publisher= |pages= |page= |date=2012-06-08 |accessdate=2012-08-24}}</ref>

==Name==
The name Veturilo was chosen in an internet contest. It is an [[Esperanto]] word meaning ''vehicle''.  Internet users submitted nearly a thousand proposals, and a jury chose a short-list of six. In the next step, during an internet vote, users chose the name Veturilo (with 32% of votes); other proposals were: Wawabike (26%),  Ziuuu (12%), Rowerynka (12%), Bajker (11%) and Wabik (6%).<ref>{{en icon}} {{cite web |author= |url=http://en.veturilo.waw.pl/2012/07/30/whats-the-origin-of-veturilo-name/|title=What<U+2019>s the origin of Veturilo name? |work=www.veturilo.waw.pl |publisher= |pages= |page= |date= |accessdate=2012-08-24}}</ref>

==System==
Bicycles are available for 9 months of the year, from 1 March to 30 November. In order to use the system, users need to register and pay a 10 [[Polish z<U+0142>oty|z<U+0142>]] initial fee. The first 20 minutes of the ride are free of charge, longer rides cost at least 1 z<U+0142>. A bicycle can be used for up to 12 hours, there is a 200 z<U+0142> fee for exceeding this limit, and after 13 hours the operator can report the bicycle as stolen to the police. The fee for the theft, loss or destruction of a bicycle is 2000 z<U+0142>.<ref>{{en icon}} {{cite web |author= |url=http://en.veturilo.waw.pl/informacje/ |title=Information |work=veturilo.waw.pl |publisher= |pages= |page= |date= |accessdate=2012-08-26}}</ref>

